60 CConfig::CConfig(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], unsigned short val_software, unsigned short val_iZone, unsigned short val_nZone, unsigned short val_nDim, unsigned short verb_level) {

164 unsigned short CConfig::GetnZone(string val_mesh_filename, unsigned short val_format, CConfig *config) {
165 
166  int nZone = 1; /* Default value if nothing is specified. */
167 
168  switch (val_format) {
169  case SU2: {
170 
171  /*--- Local variables for reading the SU2 file. ---*/
172  string text_line;
173  ifstream mesh_file;
174 
175  /*--- Check if the mesh file can be opened for reading. ---*/
176  mesh_file.open(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), ios::in);
177  if (mesh_file.fail())
178  SU2_MPI::Error(string("There is no geometry file called ") + val_mesh_filename,
179  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
180 
181  /*--- Read the SU2 mesh file until the zone data is reached or
182  when it can be decided that it is not present. ---*/
183  while( getline (mesh_file, text_line) ) {
184 
185  /*--- Search for the "NZONE" keyword to see if there are multiple Zones ---*/
186  if(text_line.find ("NZONE=",0) != string::npos) {
187  text_line.erase (0,6); nZone = atoi(text_line.c_str());
188  break;
189  }
190 
191  /*--- If one of the keywords IZONE, NELEM or NPOIN, NMARK is encountered,
192  it can be assumed that the NZONE keyword is not present and the loop
193  can be terminated. ---*/
194  if(text_line.find ("IZONE=",0) != string::npos) break;
195  if(text_line.find ("NELEM=",0) != string::npos) break;
196  if(text_line.find ("NPOIN=",0) != string::npos) break;
197  if(text_line.find ("NMARK=",0) != string::npos) break;
198  }
199 
200  mesh_file.close();
201  break;
202  }
203 
204  case CGNS: {
205 
206 #ifdef HAVE_CGNS
207 
208  /*--- Local variables which are needed when calling the CGNS mid-level API. ---*/
209  int fn, nbases, file_type;
210 
211  /*--- Check whether the supplied file is truly a CGNS file. ---*/
212  if ( cg_is_cgns(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), &file_type) != CG_OK )
213  SU2_MPI::Error(val_mesh_filename + string(" is not a CGNS file"),
214  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
215 
216  /*--- Open the CGNS file for reading. The value of fn returned
217  is the specific index number for this file and will be
218  repeatedly used in the function calls. ---*/
219  if (cg_open(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), CG_MODE_READ, &fn) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
220 
221  /*--- Get the number of databases. This is the highest node
222  in the CGNS heirarchy. ---*/
223  if (cg_nbases(fn, &nbases) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
224 
225  /*--- Check if there is more than one database. Throw an
226  error if there is because this reader can currently
227  only handle one database. ---*/
228  if ( nbases > 1 )
229  SU2_MPI::Error("CGNS reader currently incapable of handling more than 1 database.",
230  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
231 
232  /*--- Determine the number of zones present in the first base.
233  Note that the indexing starts at 1 in CGNS. Afterwards
234  close the file again. ---*/
235  if(cg_nzones(fn, 1, &nZone) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
236  if (cg_close(fn) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
237 #endif
238 
239  break;
240  }
241  }
242 
243  return (unsigned short) nZone;
244 }
245 
246 unsigned short CConfig::GetnDim(string val_mesh_filename, unsigned short val_format) {
247 
248  short nDim = -1;
249 
250  switch (val_format) {
251  case SU2: {
252 
253  /*--- Local variables for reading the SU2 file. ---*/
254  string text_line;
255  ifstream mesh_file;
256 
257  /*--- Open grid file ---*/
258  mesh_file.open(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), ios::in);
259  if (mesh_file.fail()) {
260  SU2_MPI::Error(string("The SU2 mesh file named ") + val_mesh_filename + string(" was not found."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
261  }
262 
263  /*--- Read the SU2 mesh file until the dimension data is reached
264  or when it can be decided that it is not present. ---*/
265  while( getline (mesh_file, text_line) ) {
266 
267  /*--- Search for the "NDIME" keyword to determine the number
268  of dimensions. ---*/
269  if(text_line.find ("NDIME=",0) != string::npos) {
270  text_line.erase (0,6); nDim = atoi(text_line.c_str());
271  break;
272  }
273 
274  /*--- If one of the keywords NELEM or NPOIN, NMARK is encountered,
275  it can be assumed that the NZONE keyword is not present and
276  the loop can be terminated. ---*/
277  if(text_line.find ("NELEM=",0) != string::npos) break;
278  if(text_line.find ("NPOIN=",0) != string::npos) break;
279  if(text_line.find ("NMARK=",0) != string::npos) break;
280  }
281 
282  mesh_file.close();
283 
284  /*--- Throw an error if the dimension was not found. ---*/
285  if (nDim == -1) {
286  SU2_MPI::Error(val_mesh_filename + string(" is not an SU2 mesh file or has the wrong format \n ('NDIME=' not found). Please check."),
287  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
288  }
289 
290  break;
291  }
292 
293  case CGNS: {
294 
295 #ifdef HAVE_CGNS
296 
297  /*--- Local variables which are needed when calling the CGNS mid-level API. ---*/
298  int fn, nbases, file_type;
299  int cell_dim, phys_dim;
300  char basename[CGNS_STRING_SIZE];
301 
302  /*--- Check whether the supplied file is truly a CGNS file. ---*/
303  if ( cg_is_cgns(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), &file_type) != CG_OK ) {
304  SU2_MPI::Error(val_mesh_filename + string(" was not found or is not a CGNS file."),
305  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
306  }
307 
308  /*--- Open the CGNS file for reading. The value of fn returned
309  is the specific index number for this file and will be
310  repeatedly used in the function calls. ---*/
311  if (cg_open(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), CG_MODE_READ, &fn) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
312 
313  /*--- Get the number of databases. This is the highest node
314  in the CGNS heirarchy. ---*/
315  if (cg_nbases(fn, &nbases) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
316 
317  /*--- Check if there is more than one database. Throw an
318  error if there is because this reader can currently
319  only handle one database. ---*/
320  if ( nbases > 1 )
321  SU2_MPI::Error("CGNS reader currently incapable of handling more than 1 database." ,
322  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
323 
324  /*--- Read the database. Note that the indexing starts at 1.
325  Afterwards close the file again. ---*/
326  if (cg_base_read(fn, 1, basename, &cell_dim, &phys_dim) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
327  if (cg_close(fn) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
328 
329  /*--- Set the problem dimension as read from the CGNS file ---*/
330  nDim = cell_dim;
331 #endif
332 
333  break;
334  }
335  }
336 
337  /*--- After reading the mesh, assert that the dimension is equal to 2 or 3. ---*/
338  assert((nDim == 2) || (nDim == 3));
339 
340  return (unsigned short) nDim;
341 }

344 bool CConfig::GetPeriodic(string val_mesh_filename,
345  unsigned short val_format,
346  CConfig *config) {
347 
348  bool isPeriodic = false;
349 
350  /*--- For now, assume that if we have periodic BCs in the config, that
351  the user's intent is for there to be periodic BCs in the mesh too. ---*/
352 
353  if (config->GetnMarker_Periodic() > 0) isPeriodic = true;
354 
355  return isPeriodic;
356

635 void CConfig::SetRunTime_Options(void) {
636 
637  /* DESCRIPTION: Number of external iterations */
638

2282 void CConfig::SetConfig_Parsing(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE]) {
2283  string text_line, option_name;
2284  ifstream case_file;
2285  vector<string> option_value;
2286 
2287  /*--- Read the configuration file ---*/
2288 
2289  case_file.open(case_filename, ios::in);
2290 
2291  if (case_file.fail()) {
2292  SU2_MPI::Error("The configuration file (.cfg) is missing!!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2293  }
2294 
2295  string errorString;
2296 
2297  int err_count = 0; // How many errors have we found in the config file
2298  int max_err_count = 30; // Maximum number of errors to print before stopping
2299 
2300  map<string, bool> included_options;
2301 
2302  /*--- Parse the configuration file and set the options ---*/
2303 
2304  while (getline (case_file, text_line)) {
2305 
2306  if (err_count >= max_err_count) {
2307  errorString.append("too many errors. Stopping parse");
2308 
2309  cout << errorString << endl;
2310  throw(1);
2311  }
2312 
2313  if (TokenizeString(text_line, option_name, option_value)) {
2314 
2315  /*--- See if it's a python option ---*/
2316 
2317  if (option_map.find(option_name) == option_map.end()) {
2318  string newString;
2319  newString.append(option_name);
2320  newString.append(": invalid option name");
2321  newString.append(". Check current SU2 options in config_template.cfg.");
2322  newString.append("\n");
2323  if (!option_name.compare("AD_COEFF_FLOW")) newString.append("AD_COEFF_FLOW= (1st, 2nd, 4th) is now JST_SENSOR_COEFF= (2nd, 4th).\n");
2324  if (!option_name.compare("AD_COEFF_ADJFLOW")) newString.append("AD_COEFF_ADJFLOW= (1st, 2nd, 4th) is now ADJ_JST_SENSOR_COEFF= (2nd, 4th).\n");
2325  if (!option_name.compare("SPATIAL_ORDER_FLOW")) newString.append("SPATIAL_ORDER_FLOW is now the boolean MUSCL_FLOW and the appropriate SLOPE_LIMITER_FLOW.\n");
2326  if (!option_name.compare("SPATIAL_ORDER_ADJFLOW")) newString.append("SPATIAL_ORDER_ADJFLOW is now the boolean MUSCL_ADJFLOW and the appropriate SLOPE_LIMITER_ADJFLOW.\n");
2327  if (!option_name.compare("SPATIAL_ORDER_TURB")) newString.append("SPATIAL_ORDER_TURB is now the boolean MUSCL_TURB and the appropriate SLOPE_LIMITER_TURB.\n");
2328  if (!option_name.compare("SPATIAL_ORDER_ADJTURB")) newString.append("SPATIAL_ORDER_ADJTURB is now the boolean MUSCL_ADJTURB and the appropriate SLOPE_LIMITER_ADJTURB.\n");
2329  if (!option_name.compare("LIMITER_COEFF")) newString.append("LIMITER_COEFF is now VENKAT_LIMITER_COEFF.\n");
2330  if (!option_name.compare("SHARP_EDGES_COEFF")) newString.append("SHARP_EDGES_COEFF is now ADJ_SHARP_LIMITER_COEFF.\n");
2331  if (!option_name.compare("MOTION_FILENAME")) newString.append("MOTION_FILENAME is now DV_FILENAME.\n");
2332  errorString.append(newString);
2333  err_count++;
2334  continue;
2335  }
2336 
2337  /*--- Option exists, check if the option has already been in the config file ---*/
2338 
2339  if (included_options.find(option_name) != included_options.end()) {
2340  string newString;
2341  newString.append(option_name);
2342  newString.append(": option appears twice");
2343  newString.append("\n");
2344  errorString.append(newString);
2345  err_count++;
2346  continue;
2347  }
2348 
2349 
2350  /*--- New found option. Add it to the map, and delete from all options ---*/
2351 
2352  included_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(option_name, true));
2353  all_options.erase(option_name);
2354 
2355  /*--- Set the value and check error ---*/
2356 
2357  string out = option_map[option_name]->SetValue(option_value);
2358  if (out.compare("") != 0) {
2359  errorString.append(out);
2360  errorString.append("\n");
2361  err_count++;
2362  }
2363  }
2364  }
2365 
2366  /*--- See if there were any errors parsing the config file ---*/
2367 
2368  if (errorString.size() != 0) {
2369  SU2_MPI::Error(errorString, CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2370  }
2371 
2372  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
2373 
2374  for (map<string, bool>::iterator iter = all_options.begin(); iter != all_options.end(); ++iter) {
2375  option_map[iter->first]->SetDefault();
2376  }
2377 
2378  case_file.close();
2379 
2380 }
2381 
2382 bool CConfig::SetRunTime_Parsing(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE]) {
2383  string text_line, option_name;
2384  ifstream case_file;
2385  vector<string> option_value;
2386 
2387  /*--- Read the configuration file ---*/
2388 
2389  case_file.open(case_filename, ios::in);
2390 
2391  if (case_file.fail()) { return false; }
2392 
2393  string errorString;
2394 
2395  int err_count = 0; // How many errors have we found in the config file
2396  int max_err_count = 30; // Maximum number of errors to print before stopping
2397 
2398  map<string, bool> included_options;
2399 
2400  /*--- Parse the configuration file and set the options ---*/
2401 
2402  while (getline (case_file, text_line)) {
2403 
2404  if (err_count >= max_err_count) {
2405  errorString.append("too many errors. Stopping parse");
2406 
2407  cout << errorString << endl;
2408  throw(1);
2409  }
2410 
2411  if (TokenizeString(text_line, option_name, option_value)) {
2412 
2413  if (option_map.find(option_name) == option_map.end()) {
2414 
2415  /*--- See if it's a python option ---*/
2416 
2417  string newString;
2418  newString.append(option_name);
2419  newString.append(": invalid option name");
2420  newString.append("\n");
2421  errorString.append(newString);
2422  err_count++;
2423  continue;
2424  }
2425 
2426  /*--- Option exists, check if the option has already been in the config file ---*/
2427 
2428  if (included_options.find(option_name) != included_options.end()) {
2429  string newString;
2430  newString.append(option_name);
2431  newString.append(": option appears twice");
2432  newString.append("\n");
2433  errorString.append(newString);
2434  err_count++;
2435  continue;
2436  }
2437 
2438  /*--- New found option. Add it to the map, and delete from all options ---*/
2439 
2440  included_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(option_name, true));
2441  all_options.erase(option_name);
2442 
2443  /*--- Set the value and check error ---*/
2444 
2445  string out = option_map[option_name]->SetValue(option_value);
2446  if (out.compare("") != 0) {
2447  errorString.append(out);
2448  errorString.append("\n");
2449  err_count++;
2450  }
2451 
2452  }
2453  }
2454 
2455  /*--- See if there were any errors parsing the runtime file ---*/
2456 
2457  if (errorString.size() != 0) {
2458  SU2_MPI::Error(errorString, CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2459  }
2460 
2461  case_file.close();
2462 
2463  return true;
2464 
2465 }

2467 void CConfig::SetPostprocessing(unsigned short val_software, unsigned short val_izone, unsigned short val_nDim) {
2468 
2469  unsigned short iZone, iCFL, iMarker;
2470  bool ideal_gas = ((Kind_FluidModel == STANDARD_AIR) ||
2471  (Kind_FluidModel == IDEAL_GAS) ||
2472  (Kind_FluidModel == INC_IDEAL_GAS) ||
2473  (Kind_FluidModel == CONSTANT_DENSITY));
2474  bool standard_air = ((Kind_FluidModel == STANDARD_AIR));
2475 
2476 #ifndef HAVE_TECIO
2477  if (Output_FileFormat == TECPLOT_BINARY) {
2478  cout << "Tecplot binary file requested but SU2 was built without TecIO support." << "\n";
2479  Output_FileFormat = TECPLOT;
2480  }
2481 #endif
2482 
2483  /*--- Set the boolean Wall_Functions equal to true if there is a
2484  definition for the wall founctions ---*/
2485 
2486  Wall_Functions = false;
2487  if (nMarker_WallFunctions > 0) {
2488  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_WallFunctions; iMarker++) {
2489  if (Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] != NO_WALL_FUNCTION)
2490  Wall_Functions = true;
2491 
2492  if ((Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] == ADAPTIVE_WALL_FUNCTION) || (Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] == SCALABLE_WALL_FUNCTION)
2493  || (Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] == NONEQUILIBRIUM_WALL_MODEL))
2494 
2495  SU2_MPI::Error(string("For RANS problems, use NO_WALL_FUNCTION, STANDARD_WALL_FUNCTION or EQUILIBRIUM_WALL_MODEL.\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2496 
2497  }
2498  }
2499 
2500  /*--- Fixed CM mode requires a static movement of the grid ---*/
2501 
2502  if (Fixed_CM_Mode) {
2503  Grid_Movement= true;
2504  nGridMovement = 1;
2505  Kind_GridMovement = new unsigned short[nGridMovement];
2506  Kind_GridMovement[0] = MOVING_HTP;
2507  }
2508 
2509  /*--- Initialize the AoA and Sideslip variables for the incompressible
2510  solver. This is typically unused (often internal flows). This also
2511  is necessary to avoid any issues with the AoA adjustments for the
2512  compressible code for fixed lift mode (including the adjoint). ---*/
2513 
2514  if (Kind_Regime == INCOMPRESSIBLE) {
2515 
2516  /*--- Compute x-velocity with a safegaurd for 0.0. ---*/
2517 
2518  su2double Vx = 1e-10;
2519  if (Inc_Velocity_Init[0] != 0.0) {
2520  Vx = Inc_Velocity_Init[0];
2521  }
2522 
2523  /*--- Compute the angle-of-attack and sideslip. ---*/
2524 
2525  su2double alpha = 0.0, beta = 0.0;
2526  if (val_nDim == 2) {
2527  alpha = atan(Inc_Velocity_Init[1]/Vx)*180.0/PI_NUMBER;
2528  } else {
2529  alpha = atan(Inc_Velocity_Init[2]/Vx)*180.0/PI_NUMBER;
2530  beta = atan(Inc_Velocity_Init[1]/Vx)*180.0/PI_NUMBER;
2531  }
2532 
2533  /*--- Set alpha and beta in the config class. ---*/
2534 
2535  SetAoA(alpha);
2536  SetAoS(beta);
2537 
2538  }
2539 
2540  /*--- By default, in 2D we should use TWOD_AIRFOIL (independenly from the input file) ---*/
2541 
2542  if (val_nDim == 2) Geo_Description = TWOD_AIRFOIL;
2543 
2544  /*--- Store the SU2 module that we are executing. ---*/
2545 
2546  Kind_SU2 = val_software;
2547 
2548  /*--- Set limiter for no MUSCL reconstructions ---*/
2549 
2550  if ((!MUSCL_Flow) || (Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow == SPACE_CENTERED)) Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow = NO_LIMITER;
2551  if ((!MUSCL_Turb) || (Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb == SPACE_CENTERED)) Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb = NO_LIMITER;
2552  if ((!MUSCL_AdjFlow) || (Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow == SPACE_CENTERED)) Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow = NO_LIMITER;
2553  if ((!MUSCL_AdjTurb) || (Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjTurb == SPACE_CENTERED)) Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjTurb = NO_LIMITER;
2554 
2555  /*--- Set the default for thrust in ActDisk ---*/
2556 
2557  if ((Kind_ActDisk == NET_THRUST) || (Kind_ActDisk == BC_THRUST)
2558  || (Kind_ActDisk == DRAG_MINUS_THRUST) || (Kind_ActDisk == MASSFLOW)
2559  || (Kind_ActDisk == POWER))
2560  ActDisk_Jump = RATIO;
2561 
2562  /*--- Error-catching and automatic array adjustments for objective, marker, and weights arrays --- */
2563 
2564  /*--- If Kind_Obj has not been specified, these arrays need to take a default --*/
2565 
2566  if (Weight_ObjFunc == NULL && Kind_ObjFunc == NULL) {
2567  Kind_ObjFunc = new unsigned short[1];
2568  Kind_ObjFunc[0] = DRAG_COEFFICIENT;
2569  Weight_ObjFunc = new su2double[1];
2570  Weight_ObjFunc[0] = 1.0;
2571  nObj=1;
2572  nObjW=1;
2573  }
2574 
2575  /*--- Maker sure that arrays are the same length ---*/
2576 
2577  if (nObj>0) {
2578  if (nMarker_Monitoring!=nObj && Marker_Monitoring!= NULL) {
2579  if (nMarker_Monitoring==1) {
2580  /*-- If only one marker was listed with multiple objectives, set that marker as the marker for each objective ---*/
2581  nMarker_Monitoring = nObj;
2582  string marker = Marker_Monitoring[0];
2583  delete[] Marker_Monitoring;
2584  Marker_Monitoring = new string[nMarker_Monitoring];
2585  for (iMarker=0; iMarker<nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++)
2586  Marker_Monitoring[iMarker] = marker;
2587  }
2588  else if(nObj==1){
2589  /*--- If one objective and more than one marker: repeat objective over each marker, evenly weighted ---*/
2590  unsigned int obj = Kind_ObjFunc[0];
2591  su2double wt=1.0;
2592  delete[] Kind_ObjFunc;
2593  if (Weight_ObjFunc!=NULL){
2594  wt = Weight_ObjFunc[0];
2595  delete[] Weight_ObjFunc;
2596  }
2597  Kind_ObjFunc = new short unsigned int[nMarker_Monitoring];
2598  Weight_ObjFunc = new su2double[nMarker_Monitoring];
2599  for (unsigned short iObj=0; iObj<nMarker_Monitoring; iObj++){
2600  Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] = obj;
2601  Weight_ObjFunc[iObj] = wt;
2602  }
2603  nObjW = nObj;
2604  }
2605  else if(nObj>1) {
2606  SU2_MPI::Error(string("When using more than one OBJECTIVE_FUNCTION, MARKER_MONITORING must be the same length or length 1.\n ") +
2607  string("For multiple surfaces per objective, either use one objective or list the objective multiple times.\n") +
2608  string("For multiple objectives per marker either use one marker or list the marker multiple times.\n")+
2609  string("Similar rules apply for multi-objective optimization using OPT_OBJECTIVE rather than OBJECTIVE_FUNCTION."),
2610  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2611  }
2612  }
2613  }
2614 
2615  /*-- Correct for case where Weight_ObjFunc has not been provided or has length < kind_objfunc---*/
2616 
2617  if (nObjW<nObj) {
2618  if (Weight_ObjFunc!= NULL && nObjW>1) {
2619  SU2_MPI::Error(string("The option OBJECTIVE_WEIGHT must either have the same length as OBJECTIVE_FUNCTION,\n") +
2620  string("be lenght 1, or be deleted from the config file (equal weights will be applied)."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2621  }
2622  Weight_ObjFunc = new su2double[nObj];
2623  for (unsigned short iObj=0; iObj<nObj; iObj++)
2624  Weight_ObjFunc[iObj] = 1.0;
2625  }
2626 
2627  /*--- One final check for multi-objective with the set of objectives
2628  that are not counted per-surface. We will disable multi-objective here. ---*/
2629 
2630  if (nObj > 1) {
2631  unsigned short Obj_0 = Kind_ObjFunc[0];
2632  for (unsigned short iObj=1; iObj<nObj; iObj++){
2633  switch(Kind_ObjFunc[iObj]) {
2634  case INVERSE_DESIGN_PRESSURE:
2635  case INVERSE_DESIGN_HEATFLUX:
2636  case THRUST_COEFFICIENT:
2637  case TORQUE_COEFFICIENT:
2638  case FIGURE_OF_MERIT:
2639  case SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE:
2640  case SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE:
2641  case SURFACE_MASSFLOW:
2642  case SURFACE_UNIFORMITY:
2643  case SURFACE_SECONDARY:
2644  case SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION:
2645  case SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM:
2646  case SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP:
2647  case CUSTOM_OBJFUNC:
2648  if (Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] != Obj_0) {
2649  SU2_MPI::Error(string("The following objectives can only be used for the first surface in a multi-objective \n")+
2650  string("problem or as a single objective applied to multiple monitoring markers:\n")+
2651  string("INVERSE_DESIGN_PRESSURE, INVERSE_DESIGN_HEATFLUX, THRUST_COEFFICIENT, TORQUE_COEFFICIENT\n")+
2652  string("FIGURE_OF_MERIT, SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE, SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE, SURFACE_MASSFLOW\n")+
2653  string("SURFACE_UNIFORMITY, SURFACE_SECONDARY, SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION, SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM\n")+
2654  string("SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP, CUSTOM_OBJFUNC.\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2655  }
2656  break;
2657  default:
2658  break;
2659  }
2660  }
2661  }
2662 
2663  /*--- Low memory only for ASCII Tecplot ---*/
2664 
2665  if (Output_FileFormat != TECPLOT) Low_MemoryOutput = NO;
2666 
2667  /*--- The that Discard_InFiles is false, owerwise the gradient could be wrong ---*/
2668 
2669  if ((ContinuousAdjoint || DiscreteAdjoint) && Fixed_CL_Mode && !Eval_dOF_dCX)
2670  Discard_InFiles = false;
2671 
2672  /*--- Deactivate the multigrid in the adjoint problem ---*/
2673 
2674  if ((ContinuousAdjoint && !MG_AdjointFlow) ||
2675  (Unsteady_Simulation == TIME_STEPPING)) { nMGLevels = 0; }
2676 
2677  /*--- If Fluid Structure Interaction, set the solver for each zone.
2678  *--- ZONE_0 is the zone of the fluid.
2679  *--- All the other zones are structure.
2680  *--- This will allow us to define multiple physics structural problems */
2681 
2682  if (Kind_Solver == FLUID_STRUCTURE_INTERACTION) {
2683  if (val_izone == 0) {Kind_Solver = Kind_Solver_Fluid_FSI; FSI_Problem = true;}
2684 
2685  else {Kind_Solver = Kind_Solver_Struc_FSI; FSI_Problem = true;
2686  Kind_Linear_Solver = Kind_Linear_Solver_FSI_Struc;
2687  Kind_Linear_Solver_Prec = Kind_Linear_Solver_Prec_FSI_Struc;
2688  Linear_Solver_Error = Linear_Solver_Error_FSI_Struc;
2689  Linear_Solver_Iter = Linear_Solver_Iter_FSI_Struc;
2690  // Discrete adjoint linear solver
2691  Kind_DiscAdj_Linear_Solver = Kind_DiscAdj_Linear_Solver_FSI_Struc;
2692  Kind_DiscAdj_Linear_Prec = Kind_DiscAdj_Linear_Prec_FSI_Struc;}
2693  }
2694  else { FSI_Problem = false; }
2695 
2696  if(Kind_Solver == HEAT_EQUATION_FVM) {
2697  Linear_Solver_Iter = Linear_Solver_Iter_Heat;
2698  Linear_Solver_Error = Linear_Solver_Error_Heat;
2699  }
2700 
2701  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && ContinuousAdjoint && (Ref_NonDim == DIMENSIONAL) && (Kind_SU2 == SU2_CFD)) {
2702  cout << "WARNING: The adjoint solver should use a non-dimensional flow solution." << endl;
2703  }
2704 
2705  /*--- Initialize non-physical points/reconstructions to zero ---*/
2706 
2707  Nonphys_Points = 0;
2708  Nonphys_Reconstr = 0;
2709 
2710  /*--- Set the number of external iterations to 1 for the steady state problem ---*/
2711 
2712  if (Kind_Solver == FEM_ELASTICITY) {
2713  nMGLevels = 0;
2714  if (Dynamic_Analysis == STATIC)
2715  nExtIter = 1;
2716  }
2717 
2718  /*--- Initialize the ofstream ConvHistFile. ---*/
2719  ofstream ConvHistFile;
2720 
2721  /*--- Decide whether we should be writing unsteady solution files. ---*/
2722 
2723  if (Unsteady_Simulation == STEADY ||
2724  Unsteady_Simulation == HARMONIC_BALANCE)
2725  { Wrt_Unsteady = false; }
2726  else { Wrt_Unsteady = true; }
2727 
2728  if (Kind_Solver == FEM_ELASTICITY) {
2729 
2730  if (Dynamic_Analysis == STATIC) { Wrt_Dynamic = false; }
2731  else { Wrt_Dynamic = true; }
2732 
2733  } else {
2734  Wrt_Dynamic = false;
2735  }
2736 
2737  if (Kind_Solver == ZONE_SPECIFIC) {
2738 
2739  ZoneSpecific_Problem = true;
2740  Kind_Solver = Kind_Solver_PerZone[val_izone];
2741  }
2742 
2743  /*--- Check for unsupported features. ---*/
2744 
2745  if ((Kind_Regime == INCOMPRESSIBLE) && (Unsteady_Simulation == HARMONIC_BALANCE)){
2746  SU2_MPI::Error("Harmonic Balance not yet implemented for the incompressible solver.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2747  }
2748 
2749  if ((Kind_Regime == EULER) && (Buffet_Monitoring == true)){
2750  SU2_MPI::Error("Buffet monitoring incompatible with Euler Solver", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2751  }
2752 
2753  /*--- Check for Fluid model consistency ---*/
2754 
2755  if (standard_air) {
2756  if (Gamma != 1.4 || Gas_Constant != 287.058) {
2757  Gamma = 1.4;
2758  Gas_Constant = 287.058;
2759  }
2760  }
2761 
2762  /*--- Overrule the default values for viscosity if the US measurement system is used. ---*/
2763 
2764  if (SystemMeasurements == US) {
2765 
2766  /* Correct the viscosities, if they contain the default SI values. */
2767  if(fabs(Mu_Constant-1.716E-5) < 1.0E-15) Mu_Constant /= 47.88025898;
2768  if(fabs(Mu_Ref-1.716E-5) < 1.0E-15) Mu_Ref /= 47.88025898;
2769 
2770  /* Correct the values with temperature dimension, if they contain the default SI values. */
2771  if(fabs(Mu_Temperature_Ref-273.15) < 1.0E-8) Mu_Temperature_Ref *= 1.8;
2772  if(fabs(Mu_S-110.4) < 1.0E-8) Mu_S *= 1.8;
2773 
2774  /* Correct the thermal conductivity, if it contains the default SI value. */
2775  if(fabs(Kt_Constant-0.0257) < 1.0E-10) Kt_Constant *= 0.577789317;
2776  }
2777 
2778  /*--- Check for Measurement System ---*/
2779 
2780  if (SystemMeasurements == US && !standard_air) {
2781  SU2_MPI::Error("Only STANDARD_AIR fluid model can be used with US Measurement System", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2782  }
2783 
2784  /*--- Check for Convective scheme available for NICFD ---*/
2785 
2786  if (!ideal_gas) {
2787  if (Kind_Upwind_Flow != ROE && Kind_Upwind_Flow != HLLC && Kind_Centered_Flow != JST) {
2788  SU2_MPI::Error("Only ROE Upwind, HLLC Upwind scheme, and JST scheme can be used for Non-Ideal Compressible Fluids", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2789  }
2790 
2791  }
2792 
2793  if(GetBoolTurbomachinery()){
2794  nBlades = new su2double[nZone];
2795  FreeStreamTurboNormal= new su2double[3];
2796  }
2797 
2798  /*--- Check if Giles are used with turbo markers ---*/
2799 
2800  if (nMarker_Giles > 0 && !GetBoolTurbomachinery()){
2801  SU2_MPI::Error("Giles Boundary conditions can only be used with turbomachinery markers", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2802  }
2803 
2804  /*--- Check for Boundary condition available for NICFD ---*/
2805 
2806  if (!ideal_gas) {
2807  if (nMarker_Inlet != 0) {
2808  SU2_MPI::Error("Riemann Boundary conditions or Giles must be used for inlet and outlet with Not Ideal Compressible Fluids ", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2809  }
2810  if (nMarker_Outlet != 0) {
2811  SU2_MPI::Error("Riemann Boundary conditions or Giles must be used outlet with Not Ideal Compressible Fluids ", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2812  }
2813 
2814  if (nMarker_FarField != 0) {
2815  SU2_MPI::Error("Riemann Boundary conditions or Giles must be used outlet with Not Ideal Compressible Fluids ", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2816  }
2817 
2818  }
2819 
2820  /*--- Check for Boundary condition available for NICF ---*/
2821 
2822  if (ideal_gas && (Kind_Regime != INCOMPRESSIBLE)) {
2823  if (SystemMeasurements == US && standard_air) {
2824  if (Kind_ViscosityModel != SUTHERLAND) {
2825  SU2_MPI::Error("Only SUTHERLAND viscosity model can be used with US Measurement", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2826  }
2827  }
2828  if (Kind_ConductivityModel != CONSTANT_PRANDTL ) {
2829  SU2_MPI::Error("Only CONSTANT_PRANDTL thermal conductivity model can be used with STANDARD_AIR and IDEAL_GAS", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2830  }
2831 
2832  }
2833 
2834  /*--- Force number of span-wise section to 1 if 2D case ---*/
2835  if(val_nDim ==2){
2836  nSpanWiseSections_User=1;
2837  Kind_SpanWise= EQUISPACED;
2838  }
2839 
2840  /*--- Set number of TurboPerformance markers ---*/
2841  if(nMarker_Turbomachinery > 0){
2842  if(nMarker_Turbomachinery > 1){
2843  nMarker_TurboPerformance = nMarker_Turbomachinery + SU2_TYPE::Int(nMarker_Turbomachinery/2) + 1;
2844  }else{
2845  nMarker_TurboPerformance = nMarker_Turbomachinery;
2846  }
2847  } else {
2848  nMarker_TurboPerformance = 0;
2849  nSpanWiseSections =1;
2850  }
2851 
2852  /*--- Set number of TurboPerformance markers ---*/
2853  if(nMarker_Turbomachinery != 0){
2854  nSpan_iZones = new unsigned short[nZone];
2855  }
2856 
2857  /*--- Set number of TurboPerformance markers ---*/
2858  if(RampRotatingFrame && !DiscreteAdjoint){
2859  FinalRotation_Rate_Z = new su2double[nZone];
2860  for(iZone=0; iZone <nZone; iZone ++){
2861  FinalRotation_Rate_Z[iZone] = Rotation_Rate_Z[iZone];
2862  if(abs(FinalRotation_Rate_Z[iZone]) > 0.0){
2863  Rotation_Rate_Z[iZone] = RampRotatingFrame_Coeff[0];
2864  }
2865  }
2866  }
2867 
2868  if(RampOutletPressure && !DiscreteAdjoint){
2869  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Giles; iMarker++){
2870  if (Kind_Data_Giles[iMarker] == STATIC_PRESSURE || Kind_Data_Giles[iMarker] == STATIC_PRESSURE_1D || Kind_Data_Giles[iMarker] == RADIAL_EQUILIBRIUM ){
2871  FinalOutletPressure = Giles_Var1[iMarker];
2872  Giles_Var1[iMarker] = RampOutletPressure_Coeff[0];
2873  }
2874  }
2875  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Riemann; iMarker++){
2876  if (Kind_Data_Riemann[iMarker] == STATIC_PRESSURE || Kind_Data_Riemann[iMarker] == RADIAL_EQUILIBRIUM){
2877  FinalOutletPressure = Riemann_Var1[iMarker];
2878  Riemann_Var1[iMarker] = RampOutletPressure_Coeff[0];
2879  }
2880  }
2881  }
2882 
2883  /*--- Check on extra Relaxation factor for Giles---*/
2884  if(ExtraRelFacGiles[1] > 0.5){
2885  ExtraRelFacGiles[1] = 0.5;
2886  }
2887 
2888 
2889  /*--- Set grid movement kind to NO_MOVEMENT if not specified, which means
2890  that we also set the Grid_Movement flag to false. We initialize to the
2891  number of zones here, because we are guaranteed to at least have one. ---*/
2892 
2893  if (Kind_GridMovement == NULL) {
2894  Kind_GridMovement = new unsigned short[nZone];
2895  for (unsigned short iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++ )
2896  Kind_GridMovement[iZone] = NO_MOVEMENT;
2897  if (Grid_Movement == true) {
2898  SU2_MPI::Error("GRID_MOVEMENT = YES but no type provided in GRID_MOVEMENT_KIND!!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2899  }
2900  }
2901 
2902  /*--- If we're solving a purely steady problem with no prescribed grid
2903  movement (both rotating frame and moving walls can be steady), make sure that
2904  there is no grid motion ---*/
2905 
2906  if ((Kind_SU2 == SU2_CFD || Kind_SU2 == SU2_SOL) &&
2907  (Unsteady_Simulation == STEADY) &&
2908  ((Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] != MOVING_WALL) &&
2909  (Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] != ROTATING_FRAME) &&
2910  (Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] != STEADY_TRANSLATION) &&
2911  (Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] != FLUID_STRUCTURE)))
2912  Grid_Movement = false;
2913 
2914  if ((Kind_SU2 == SU2_CFD || Kind_SU2 == SU2_SOL) &&
2915  (Unsteady_Simulation == STEADY) &&
2916  ((Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] == MOVING_HTP)))
2917  Grid_Movement = true;
2918 
2919  /*--- The Line Search should be applied only in the deformation stage. ---*/
2920 
2921  if (Kind_SU2 != SU2_DEF) {
2922  Opt_RelaxFactor = 1.0;
2923  }
2924 
2925  /*--- If it is not specified, set the mesh motion mach number
2926  equal to the freestream value. ---*/
2927 
2928  if (Grid_Movement && Mach_Motion == 0.0)
2929  Mach_Motion = Mach;
2930 
2931  /*--- Set the boolean flag if we are in a rotating frame (source term). ---*/
2932 
2933  if (Grid_Movement && Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] == ROTATING_FRAME)
2934  Rotating_Frame = true;
2935  else
2936  Rotating_Frame = false;
2937 
2938  /*--- Check the number of moving markers against the number of grid movement
2939  types provided (should be equal, except that rigid motion and rotating frame
2940  do not depend on surface specification). ---*/
2941 
2942  if (Grid_Movement &&
2943  (Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] != RIGID_MOTION) &&
2944  (Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] != ROTATING_FRAME) &&
2945  (Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] != MOVING_HTP) &&
2946  (Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] != STEADY_TRANSLATION) &&
2947  (Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] != FLUID_STRUCTURE) &&
2948  (Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] != GUST) &&
2949  (nGridMovement != nMarker_Moving)) {
2950  SU2_MPI::Error("Number of GRID_MOVEMENT_KIND must match number of MARKER_MOVING!!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2951  }
2952 
2953  /*--- In case the grid movement parameters have not been declared in the
2954  config file, set them equal to zero for safety. Also check to make sure
2955  that for each option, a value has been declared for each moving marker. ---*/
2956 
2957  unsigned short nMoving;
2958  if (nGridMovement > nZone) nMoving = nGridMovement;
2959  else nMoving = nZone;
2960 
2961  /*--- Motion Origin: ---*/
2962 
2963  if (Motion_Origin_X == NULL) {
2964  Motion_Origin_X = new su2double[nMoving];
2965  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nMoving; iZone++ )
2966  Motion_Origin_X[iZone] = 0.0;
2967  } else {
2968  if (Grid_Movement && (nMotion_Origin_X != nGridMovement)) {
2969  SU2_MPI::Error("Length of MOTION_ORIGIN_X must match GRID_MOVEMENT_KIND!!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2970  }
2971  }
2972 
2973  if (Motion_Origin_Y == NULL) {
2974  Motion_Origin_Y = new su2double[nMoving];
2975  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nMoving; iZone++ )
2976  Motion_Origin_Y[iZone] = 0.0;
2977  } else {
2978  if (Grid_Movement && (nMotion_Origin_Y != nGridMovement)) {
2979  SU2_MPI::Error("Length of MOTION_ORIGIN_Y must match GRID_MOVEMENT_KIND!!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2980  }
2981  }
2982 
2983  if (Motion_Origin_Z == NULL) {
2984  Motion_Origin_Z = new su2double[nMoving];
2985  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nMoving; iZone++ )
2986  Motion_Origin_Z[iZone] = 0.0;
2987  } else {
2988  if (Grid_Movement && (nMotion_Origin_Z != nGridMovement)) {
2989  SU2_MPI::Error("Length of MOTION_ORIGIN_Z must match GRID_MOVEMENT_KIND!!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2990  }
2991  }
2992 
2993  if (MoveMotion_Origin == NULL) {
2994  MoveMotion_Origin = new unsigned short[nMoving];
2995  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nMoving; iZone++ )

4007  if (Kind_ViscosityModel == SUTHERLAND) {
4008  if ((Kind_FluidModel != INC_IDEAL_GAS)) {
4009  SU2_MPI::Error("Sutherland's law only valid for ideal gases in incompressible flows.\n Must use VISCOSITY_MODEL=CONSTANT_VISCOSITY and set viscosity with\n MU_CONSTANT, or use DENSITY_MODEL= VARIABLE with FLUID_MODEL= INC_IDEAL_GAS for VISCOSITY_MODEL=SUTHERLAND.\n NOTE: FREESTREAM_VISCOSITY is no longer used for incompressible flows!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4010  }
4011  }
4012  }
4013 
4014  /*--- Incompressible solver currently limited to SI units. ---*/
4015 
4016  if ((Kind_Regime == INCOMPRESSIBLE) && (SystemMeasurements == US)) {
4017  SU2_MPI::Error("Must use SI units for incompressible solver.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4018  }
4019 
4020  /*--- Check that the non-dim type is valid. ---*/
4021 
4022  if (Kind_Regime == INCOMPRESSIBLE) {
4023  if ((Ref_Inc_NonDim != INITIAL_VALUES) && (Ref_Inc_NonDim != REFERENCE_VALUES) && (Ref_Inc_NonDim != DIMENSIONAL)) {
4024  SU2_MPI::Error("Incompressible non-dim. scheme invalid.\n Must use INITIAL_VALUES, REFERENCE_VALUES, or DIMENSIONAL.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4025  }
4026  }
4027 
4028  /*--- If Kind_Inc_Inlet has not been specified, take a default --*/
4029 
4030  if (Kind_Inc_Inlet == NULL) {
4031  if (nMarker_Inlet != 0) {
4032  Kind_Inc_Inlet = new unsigned short[nMarker_Inlet];
4033  for (unsigned short iInlet = 0; iInlet < nMarker_Inlet; iInlet++) {
4034  Kind_Inc_Inlet[iInlet] = VELOCITY_INLET;
4035  }
4036  } else {
4037  Kind_Inc_Inlet = new unsigned short[1];
4038  Kind_Inc_Inlet[0] = VELOCITY_INLET;
4039  }
4040  }
4041 
4042  /*--- Grid motion is not yet supported with the incompressible solver. ---*/
4043 
4044  if ((Kind_Regime == INCOMPRESSIBLE) && (Grid_Movement)) {
4045  SU2_MPI::Error("Support for grid movement not yet implemented for incompressible flows.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4046  }
4047 
4048  /*--- Assert that there are two markers being analyzed if the
4049  pressure drop objective function is selected. ---*/
4050 
4051  for (unsigned short iObj = 0; iObj < nObj; iObj++) {
4052  if ((Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] == SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP) && (nMarker_Analyze != 2)) {
4053  SU2_MPI::Error("Must list two markers for the pressure drop objective function.\n Expected format: MARKER_ANALYZE= (outlet_name, inlet_name).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4054  }
4055  }
4056 
4057 }

4735  switch (Kind_Solver) {

4737  if (Kind_Regime == COMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Compressible Euler equations." << endl;
4738  if (Kind_Regime == INCOMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Incompressible Euler equations." << endl;
4739  break;

4741  if (Kind_Regime == COMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Compressible Laminar Navier-Stokes' equations." << endl;

4745  if (Kind_Regime == COMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Compressible RANS equations." << endl;
4746  if (Kind_Regime == INCOMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Incompressible RANS equations." << endl;

4750  case SA_NEG: cout << "Negative Spalart Allmaras" << endl; break;
4751  case SST: cout << "Menter's SST" << endl; break;
4752  case SA_E: cout << "Edwards Spalart Allmaras" << endl; break;
4753  case SA_COMP: cout << "Compressibility Correction Spalart Allmaras" << endl; break;
4754  case SA_E_COMP: cout << "Compressibility Correction Edwards Spalart Allmaras" << endl; break;
4755  }

4757  cout << "Hybrid RANS/LES: ";
4758  switch (Kind_HybridRANSLES){
4759  case NO_HYBRIDRANSLES: cout << "No Hybrid RANS/LES" << endl; break;
4760  case SA_DES: cout << "Detached Eddy Simulation (DES97) " << endl; break;
4761  case SA_DDES: cout << "Delayed Detached Eddy Simulation (DDES) with Standard SGS" << endl; break;
4762  case SA_ZDES: cout << "Delayed Detached Eddy Simulation (DDES) with Vorticity-based SGS" << endl; break;
4763  case SA_EDDES: cout << "Delayed Detached Eddy Simulation (DDES) with Shear-layer Adapted SGS" << endl; break;
4764  }
4765  break;
4766  case FEM_LES:
4767  if (Kind_Regime == COMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Compressible LES equations." << endl;

6307 bool CConfig::TokenizeString(string & str, string & option_name,
6308  vector<string> & option_value) {
6309  const string delimiters(" ()[]{}:,\t\n\v\f\r");
6310  // check for comments or empty string
6311  string::size_type pos, last_pos;
6312  pos = str.find_first_of("%");
6313  if ( (str.length() == 0) || (pos == 0) ) {
6314  // str is empty or a comment line, so no option here
6315  return false;
6316  }
6317  if (pos != string::npos) {
6318  // remove comment at end if necessary
6319  str.erase(pos);
6320  }
6321 
6322  // look for line composed on only delimiters (usually whitespace)
6323  pos = str.find_first_not_of(delimiters);
6324  if (pos == string::npos) {
6325  return false;
6326  }
6327 
6328  // find the equals sign and split string
6329  string name_part, value_part;
6330  pos = str.find("=");
6331  if (pos == string::npos) {
6332  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
6333  << "line in the configuration file with no \"=\" sign."
6334  << endl;
6335  cout << "Look for: " << str << endl;
6336  cout << "str.length() = " << str.length() << endl;
6337  throw(-1);
6338  }
6339  name_part = str.substr(0, pos);
6340  value_part = str.substr(pos+1, string::npos);
6341  //cout << "name_part = |" << name_part << "|" << endl;
6342  //cout << "value_part = |" << value_part << "|" << endl;
6343 
6344  // the first_part should consist of one string with no interior delimiters
6345  last_pos = name_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, 0);
6346  pos = name_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
6347  if ( (name_part.length() == 0) || (last_pos == string::npos) ) {
6348  cerr << "Error in CConfig::TokenizeString(): "
6349  << "line in the configuration file with no name before the \"=\" sign."
6350  << endl;
6351  throw(-1);
6352  }
6353  if (pos == string::npos) pos = name_part.length();
6354  option_name = name_part.substr(last_pos, pos - last_pos);
6355  last_pos = name_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, pos);
6356  if (last_pos != string::npos) {
6357  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
6358  << "two or more options before an \"=\" sign in the configuration file."
6359  << endl;
6360  throw(-1);
6361  }
6362  StringToUpperCase(option_name);
6363 
6364  //cout << "option_name = |" << option_name << "|" << endl;
6365  //cout << "pos = " << pos << ": last_pos = " << last_pos << endl;
6366 
6367  // now fill the option value vector
6368  option_value.clear();
6369  last_pos = value_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, 0);
6370  pos = value_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
6371  while (string::npos != pos || string::npos != last_pos) {
6372  // add token to the vector<string>
6373  option_value.push_back(value_part.substr(last_pos, pos - last_pos));
6374  // skip delimiters
6375  last_pos = value_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, pos);
6376  // find next "non-delimiter"
6377  pos = value_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
6378  }
6379  if (option_value.size() == 0) {
6380  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
6381  << "option " << option_name << " in configuration file with no value assigned."
6382  << endl;
6383  throw(-1);
6384  }
6385 
6386 #if 0
6387  cout << "option value(s) = ";
6388  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
6389  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
6390  cout << endl;
6391 #endif
6392 
6393  // look for ';' DV delimiters attached to values
6394  vector<string>::iterator it;
6395  it = option_value.begin();
6396  while (it != option_value.end()) {
6397  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
6398  it++;
6399  continue;
6400  }
6401 
6402  pos = it->find(';');
6403  if (pos != string::npos) {
6404  string before_semi = it->substr(0, pos);
6405  string after_semi= it->substr(pos+1, string::npos);
6406  if (before_semi.empty()) {
6407  *it = ";";
6408  it++;
6409  option_value.insert(it, after_semi);
6410  } else {
6411  *it = before_semi;
6412  it++;
6413  vector<string> to_insert;
6414  to_insert.push_back(";");
6415  if (!after_semi.empty())
6416  to_insert.push_back(after_semi);
6417  option_value.insert(it, to_insert.begin(), to_insert.end());
6418  }
6419  it = option_value.begin(); // go back to beginning; not efficient
6420  continue;
6421  } else {
6422  it++;
6423  }
6424  }
6425 #if 0
6426  cout << "option value(s) = ";
6427  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
6428  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
6429  cout << endl;
6430 #endif
6431  // remove any consecutive ";"
6432  it = option_value.begin();
6433  bool semi_at_prev = false;
6434  while (it != option_value.end()) {
6435  if (semi_at_prev) {
6436  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
6437  option_value.erase(it);
6438  it = option_value.begin();
6439  semi_at_prev = false;
6440  continue;
6441  }
6442  }
6443  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
6444  semi_at_prev = true;
6445  } else {
6446  semi_at_prev = false;
6447  }
6448  it++;
6449  }
6450 
6451 #if 0
6452  cout << "option value(s) = ";
6453  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
6454  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
6455  cout << endl;
6456 #endif
6457  return true;
6458 }

6466  return iMarker_CfgFile;
6467 
6468  SU2_MPI::Error(string("The configuration file doesn't have any definition for marker ") + val_marker, CURRENT_FUNCTION);
6469  return 0;
6470 }

6584 
6585 CConfig::~CConfig(void) {
6586 
6587  unsigned long iDV, iMarker, iPeriodic, iFFD;
6588 
6589  /*--- Delete all of the option objects in the global option map ---*/
6590 
6591  for(map<string, COptionBase*>::iterator itr = option_map.begin(); itr != option_map.end(); itr++) {
6592  delete itr->second;
6593  }
6594 
6595  if (TimeDOFsADER_DG != NULL) delete [] TimeDOFsADER_DG;
6596  if (TimeIntegrationADER_DG != NULL) delete [] TimeIntegrationADER_DG;
6597  if (WeightsIntegrationADER_DG != NULL) delete [] WeightsIntegrationADER_DG;
6598  if (RK_Alpha_Step != NULL) delete [] RK_Alpha_Step;
6599  if (MG_PreSmooth != NULL) delete [] MG_PreSmooth;
6600  if (MG_PostSmooth != NULL) delete [] MG_PostSmooth;
6601 
6602  /*--- Free memory for Aeroelastic problems. ---*/
6603 
6604  if (Grid_Movement && Aeroelastic_Simulation) {
6605  if (Aeroelastic_pitch != NULL) delete[] Aeroelastic_pitch;
6606  if (Aeroelastic_plunge != NULL) delete[] Aeroelastic_plunge;
6607  }
6608 
6609  /*--- Free memory for unspecified grid motion parameters ---*/
6610 
6611  if (Kind_GridMovement != NULL) delete [] Kind_GridMovement;
6612 
6613  /*--- Free memory for airfoil sections ---*/
6614 
6615  if (LocationStations != NULL) delete [] LocationStations;
6616 
6617  /*--- motion origin: ---*/
6618 
6619  if (Motion_Origin_X != NULL) delete [] Motion_Origin_X;
6620  if (Motion_Origin_Y != NULL) delete [] Motion_Origin_Y;
6621  if (Motion_Origin_Z != NULL) delete [] Motion_Origin_Z;
6622  if (MoveMotion_Origin != NULL) delete [] MoveMotion_Origin;
6623 
6624  /*--- translation: ---*/
6625 
6626  if (Translation_Rate_X != NULL) delete [] Translation_Rate_X;
6627  if (Translation_Rate_Y != NULL) delete [] Translation_Rate_Y;
6628  if (Translation_Rate_Z != NULL) delete [] Translation_Rate_Z;
6629 
6630  /*--- rotation: ---*/
6631

7055 string CConfig::GetUnsteady_FileName(string val_filename, int val_iter) {
7056 
7057  string UnstExt, UnstFilename = val_filename;
7058  char buffer[50];
7059 
7060  /*--- Check that a positive value iteration is requested (for now). ---*/
7061 
7062  if (val_iter < 0) {
7063  SU2_MPI::Error("Requesting a negative iteration number for the restart file!!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
7064  }
7065 
7066  /*--- Append iteration number for unsteady cases ---*/
7067 
7068  if ((Wrt_Unsteady) || (Wrt_Dynamic)) {
7069  unsigned short lastindex = UnstFilename.find_last_of(".");
7070  UnstFilename = UnstFilename.substr(0, lastindex);
7071  if ((val_iter >= 0) && (val_iter < 10)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d.dat", val_iter);
7072  if ((val_iter >= 10) && (val_iter < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d.dat", val_iter);
7073  if ((val_iter >= 100) && (val_iter < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d.dat", val_iter);
7074  if ((val_iter >= 1000) && (val_iter < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d.dat", val_iter);
7075  if (val_iter >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.dat", val_iter);
7076  string UnstExt = string(buffer);
7077  UnstFilename.append(UnstExt);
7078  }
7079 
7080  return UnstFilename;
7081 }

7137 string CConfig::GetObjFunc_Extension(string val_filename) {
7138 
7139  string AdjExt, Filename = val_filename;
7140 
7141  if (ContinuousAdjoint || DiscreteAdjoint) {
7142 
7143  /*--- Remove filename extension (.dat) ---*/
7144 
7145  unsigned short lastindex = Filename.find_last_of(".");
7146  Filename = Filename.substr(0, lastindex);
7147 
7148  if (nObj==1) {
7149  switch (Kind_ObjFunc[0]) {
7150  case DRAG_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cd"; break;
7151  case LIFT_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cl"; break;
7152  case SIDEFORCE_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_csf"; break;
7153  case INVERSE_DESIGN_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_invpress"; break;
7154  case INVERSE_DESIGN_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_invheat"; break;
7155  case MOMENT_X_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmx"; break;
7156  case MOMENT_Y_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmy"; break;
7157  case MOMENT_Z_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmz"; break;
7158  case EFFICIENCY: AdjExt = "_eff"; break;
7159  case EQUIVALENT_AREA: AdjExt = "_ea"; break;
7160  case NEARFIELD_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_nfp"; break;
7161  case FORCE_X_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfx"; break;
7162  case FORCE_Y_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfy"; break;
7163  case FORCE_Z_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfz"; break;
7164  case THRUST_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_ct"; break;
7165  case TORQUE_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cq"; break;
7166  case TOTAL_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_totheat"; break;
7167  case MAXIMUM_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_maxheat"; break;
7168  case FIGURE_OF_MERIT: AdjExt = "_merit"; break;
7169  case BLOWING_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmu"; break;
7170  case BUFFET_SENSOR: AdjExt = "_buffet"; break;
7171  case SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_pt"; break;
7172  case SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_pe"; break;
7173  case SURFACE_MASSFLOW: AdjExt = "_mfr"; break;
7174  case SURFACE_UNIFORMITY: AdjExt = "_uniform"; break;
7175  case SURFACE_SECONDARY: AdjExt = "_second"; break;
7176  case SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION: AdjExt = "_distort"; break;
7177  case SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM: AdjExt = "_sou"; break;
7178  case SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP: AdjExt = "_dp"; break;
7179  case SURFACE_MACH: AdjExt = "_mach"; break;
7180  case CUSTOM_OBJFUNC: AdjExt = "_custom"; break;
7181  case KINETIC_ENERGY_LOSS: AdjExt = "_ke"; break;
7182  case TOTAL_PRESSURE_LOSS: AdjExt = "_pl"; break;
7183  case FLOW_ANGLE_OUT: AdjExt = "_fao"; break;
7184  case FLOW_ANGLE_IN: AdjExt = "_fai"; break;
7185  case TOTAL_EFFICIENCY: AdjExt = "_teff"; break;
7186  case TOTAL_STATIC_EFFICIENCY: AdjExt = "_tseff"; break;
7187  case EULERIAN_WORK: AdjExt = "_ew"; break;
7188  case MASS_FLOW_IN: AdjExt = "_mfi"; break;
7189  case MASS_FLOW_OUT: AdjExt = "_mfo"; break;
7190  case ENTROPY_GENERATION: AdjExt = "_entg"; break;
7191  case REFERENCE_GEOMETRY: AdjExt = "_refgeom"; break;
7192  case REFERENCE_NODE: AdjExt = "_refnode"; break;
7193  }
7194  }
7195  else{
7196  AdjExt = "_combo";
7197  }
7198  Filename.append(AdjExt);
7199 
7200  /*--- Lastly, add the .dat extension ---*/
7201  Filename.append(".dat");
7202 
7203  }
7204 
7205  return Filename;
7206 }

7239 void CConfig::SetGlobalParam(unsigned short val_solver,
7240  unsigned short val_system,
7241  unsigned long val_extiter) {
7242 
7243  /*--- Set the simulation global time ---*/
7244 
7245  Current_UnstTime = static_cast<su2double>(val_extiter)*Delta_UnstTime;
7246  Current_UnstTimeND = static_cast<su2double>(val_extiter)*Delta_UnstTimeND;
7247 
7248  /*--- Set the solver methods ---*/
7249 
7250  switch (val_solver) {
7251  case EULER:
7252  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
7253  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
7254  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
7255  MUSCL_Flow, NONE);
7256  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
7257  }
7258  break;
7259  case NAVIER_STOKES:
7260  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
7261  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
7262  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
7263  MUSCL_Flow, NONE);
7264  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
7265  }
7266  if (val_system == RUNTIME_HEAT_SYS) {
7267  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Heat, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE);
7268  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Heat);
7269  }
7270  break;
7271  case RANS:
7272  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
7273  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
7274  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
7275  MUSCL_Flow, NONE);
7276  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
7277  }
7278  if (val_system == RUNTIME_TURB_SYS) {
7279  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
7280  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
7281  MUSCL_Turb, NONE);
7282  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
7283  }
7284  if (val_system == RUNTIME_TRANS_SYS) {
7285  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
7286  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
7287  MUSCL_Turb, NONE);
7288  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
7289  }
7290  if (val_system == RUNTIME_HEAT_SYS) {
7291  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Heat, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE);
7292  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Heat);
7293  }
7294  break;
7295  case FEM_EULER:
7296  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
7297  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_FEM_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
7298  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
7299  MUSCL_Flow, Kind_FEM_Flow);
7300  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_FEM_Flow);
7301  }
7302  break;
7303  case FEM_NAVIER_STOKES:
7304  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
7305  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
7306  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
7307  MUSCL_Flow, Kind_FEM_Flow);
7308  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_FEM_Flow);
7309  }
7310  break;
7311  case FEM_LES:
7312  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
7313  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
7314  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
7315  MUSCL_Flow, Kind_FEM_Flow);
7316  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_FEM_Flow);
7317  }
7318  break;
7319  case ADJ_EULER:
7320  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
7321  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
7322  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
7323  MUSCL_Flow, NONE);
7324  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
7325  }
7326  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS) {
7327  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow, Kind_Centered_AdjFlow,
7328  Kind_Upwind_AdjFlow, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow,
7329  MUSCL_AdjFlow, NONE);
7330  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjFlow);
7331  }
7332  break;
7333  case ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES:
7334  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
7335  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
7336  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
7337  MUSCL_Flow, NONE);
7338  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
7339  }
7340  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS) {
7341  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow, Kind_Centered_AdjFlow,
7342  Kind_Upwind_AdjFlow, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow,
7343  MUSCL_AdjFlow, NONE);
7344  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjFlow);
7345  }
7346  break;
7347  case ADJ_RANS:
7348  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
7349  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
7350  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
7351  MUSCL_Flow, NONE);
7352  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
7353  }
7354  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS) {
7355  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow, Kind_Centered_AdjFlow,
7356  Kind_Upwind_AdjFlow, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow,
7357  MUSCL_AdjFlow, NONE);
7358  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjFlow);
7359  }
7360  if (val_system == RUNTIME_TURB_SYS) {
7361  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
7362  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
7363  MUSCL_Turb, NONE);
7364  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
7365  }
7366  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJTURB_SYS) {
7367  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjTurb, Kind_Centered_AdjTurb,
7368  Kind_Upwind_AdjTurb, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjTurb,
7369  MUSCL_AdjTurb, NONE);
7370  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjTurb);
7371  }
7372  break;
7373  case HEAT_EQUATION_FVM:
7374  if (val_system == RUNTIME_HEAT_SYS) {
7375  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE);
7376  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Heat);
7377  }
7378  break;
7379 
7380  case FEM_ELASTICITY:
7381 
7382  Current_DynTime = static_cast<su2double>(val_extiter)*Delta_DynTime;
7383 
7384  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FEA_SYS) {
7385  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE);
7386  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_FEA);
7387  }
7388  break;
7389  }
7390 }

7413 unsigned short CConfig::GetMarker_Periodic_Donor(string val_marker) {
7414  unsigned short iMarker_PerBound, jMarker_PerBound, kMarker_All;
7415 
7416  /*--- Find the marker for this periodic boundary. ---*/
7417  for (iMarker_PerBound = 0; iMarker_PerBound < nMarker_PerBound; iMarker_PerBound++)
7418  if (Marker_PerBound[iMarker_PerBound] == val_marker) break;
7419 
7420  /*--- Find corresponding donor. ---*/
7421  for (jMarker_PerBound = 0; jMarker_PerBound < nMarker_PerBound; jMarker_PerBound++)
7422  if (Marker_PerBound[jMarker_PerBound] == Marker_PerDonor[iMarker_PerBound]) break;
7423 
7424  /*--- Find and return global marker index for donor boundary. ---*/
7425  for (kMarker_All = 0; kMarker_All < nMarker_CfgFile; kMarker_All++)
7426  if (Marker_PerBound[jMarker_PerBound] == Marker_All_TagBound[kMarker_All]) break;
7427 
7428  return kMarker_All;
7429 }

7527 su2double CConfig::GetActDisk_TempJump(string val_marker, unsigned short val_value) {

8020  unsigned short iDV;
8021  unsigned short iMarker_Transpiration = 0, iMarker_DV = 0;
8022 
8023  if (nMarker_Transpiration > 0 && nDV > 0) {
8024  for(iDV = 0; iDV < nDV; iDV++){
8025  if(Design_Variable[iDV] == TRANSP_DV){
8026  for (iMarker_Transpiration = 0; iMarker_Transpiration< nMarker_Transpiration; iMarker_Transpiration++){
8027  if (TranspTag[iDV] == Marker_Transpiration[iMarker_Transpiration]){
8028  Transx0[iMarker_Transpiration] = ParamDV[iDV][1];
8029  Transx1[iMarker_Transpiration] = ParamDV[iDV][2];
8030  Transx2[iMarker_Transpiration] = ParamDV[iDV][3];
8031  Transx3[iMarker_Transpiration] = ParamDV[iDV][4];
8032  Transy0[iMarker_Transpiration] = ParamDV[iDV][5];
8033  Transy1[iMarker_Transpiration] = ParamDV[iDV][6];
8034  Transy2[iMarker_Transpiration] = ParamDV[iDV][7];
8035  Transy3[iMarker_Transpiration] = ParamDV[iDV][8];
8036  TransEps0[iMarker_Transpiration] = DV_Value[iDV][0];
8037  TransEps1[iMarker_Transpiration] = DV_Value[iDV][1];
8038  TransEps2[iMarker_Transpiration] = DV_Value[iDV][2];
8039  TransEps3[iMarker_Transpiration] = DV_Value[iDV][3];
8040  }
8041  }
8042  }
8043  }
8044  }
8045 }

8421 
8422 void CConfig::SetSpline(vector<su2double> &x, vector<su2double> &y, unsigned long n, su2double yp1, su2double ypn, vector<su2double> &y2) {
8423  unsigned long i, k;
8424  su2double p, qn, sig, un, *u;
8425 
8426  u = new su2double [n];
8427 
8428  if (yp1 > 0.99e30) // The lower boundary condition is set either to be "nat
8429  y2[0]=u[0]=0.0; // -ural"
8430  else { // or else to have a specified first derivative.
8431  y2[0] = -0.5;
8432  u[0]=(3.0/(x[1]-x[0]))*((y[1]-y[0])/(x[1]-x[0])-yp1);
8433  }
8434 
8435  for (i=2; i<=n-1; i++) { // This is the decomposition loop of the tridiagonal al-
8436  sig=(x[i-1]-x[i-2])/(x[i]-x[i-2]); // gorithm. y2 and u are used for tem-
8437  p=sig*y2[i-2]+2.0; // porary storage of the decomposed
8438  y2[i-1]=(sig-1.0)/p; // factors.
8439  u[i-1]=(y[i]-y[i-1])/(x[i]-x[i-1]) - (y[i-1]-y[i-2])/(x[i-1]-x[i-2]);
8440  u[i-1]=(6.0*u[i-1]/(x[i]-x[i-2])-sig*u[i-2])/p;
8441  }
8442 
8443  if (ypn > 0.99e30) // The upper boundary condition is set either to be
8444  qn=un=0.0; // "natural"
8445  else { // or else to have a specified first derivative.
8446  qn=0.5;
8447  un=(3.0/(x[n-1]-x[n-2]))*(ypn-(y[n-1]-y[n-2])/(x[n-1]-x[n-2]));
8448  }
8449  y2[n-1]=(un-qn*u[n-2])/(qn*y2[n-2]+1.0);
8450  for (k=n-1; k>=1; k--) // This is the backsubstitution loop of the tridiagonal
8451  y2[k-1]=y2[k-1]*y2[k]+u[k-1]; // algorithm.
8452 
8453  delete[] u;
8454 
8455 }
8456 
8457 su2double CConfig::GetSpline(vector<su2double>&xa, vector<su2double>&ya, vector<su2double>&y2a, unsigned long n, su2double x) {
8458  unsigned long klo, khi, k;
8459  su2double h, b, a, y;
8460 
8461  klo=1; // We will find the right place in the table by means of
8462  khi=n; // bisection. This is optimal if sequential calls to this
8463  while (khi-klo > 1) { // routine are at random values of x. If sequential calls
8464  k=(khi+klo) >> 1; // are in order, and closely spaced, one would do better
8465  if (xa[k-1] > x) khi=k; // to store previous values of klo and khi and test if
8466  else klo=k; // they remain appropriate on the next call.
8467  } // klo and khi now bracket the input value of x
8468  h=xa[khi-1]-xa[klo-1];
8469  if (h == 0.0) cout << "Bad xa input to routine splint" << endl; // The xa?s must be dis-
8470  a=(xa[khi-1]-x)/h; // tinct.
8471  b=(x-xa[klo-1])/h; // Cubic spline polynomial is now evaluated.
8472  y=a*ya[klo-1]+b*ya[khi-1]+((a*a*a-a)*y2a[klo-1]+(b*b*b-b)*y2a[khi-1])*(h*h)/6.0;
8473 
8474  return y;
8475 }

8490 void CConfig::Tock(double val_start_time, string val_function_name, int val_group_id) {

8493 
8494  double val_stop_time = 0.0, val_elapsed_time = 0.0;
8495 
8496 #ifndef HAVE_MPI
8497  val_stop_time = double(clock())/double(CLOCKS_PER_SEC);
8498 #else
8499  val_stop_time = MPI_Wtime();
8500 #endif
8501

8503  val_elapsed_time = val_stop_time - val_start_time;
8504 
8505  /*--- Store the subroutine name and the elapsed time ---*/
8506  Profile_Function_tp.push_back(val_function_name);
8507  Profile_Time_tp.push_back(val_elapsed_time);

8514 void CConfig::SetProfilingCSV(void) {
8515 
8516 #ifdef PROFILE
8517 
8518  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
8519  int size = SINGLE_NODE;
8520 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
8521  SU2_MPI::Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
8522  SU2_MPI::Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &size);
8523 #endif
8524 
8525  /*--- Each rank has the same stack trace, so the they have the same
8526  function calls and ordering in the vectors. We're going to reduce
8527  the timings from each rank and extract the avg, min, and max timings. ---*/
8528 
8529  /*--- First, create a local mapping, so that we can extract the
8530  min and max values for each function. ---*/
8531 
8532  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < Profile_Function_tp.size(); i++) {
8533 
8534  /*--- Add the function and initialize if not already stored (the ID
8535  only needs to be stored the first time).---*/
8536  if (Profile_Map_tp.find(Profile_Function_tp[i]) == Profile_Map_tp.end()) {
8537 
8538  vector<int> profile; profile.push_back(i);
8539  Profile_Map_tp.insert(pair<string,vector<int> >(Profile_Function_tp[i],profile));
8540 
8541  } else {
8542 
8543  /*--- This function has already been added, so simply increment the
8544  number of calls and total time for this function. ---*/
8545 
8546  Profile_Map_tp[Profile_Function_tp[i]].push_back(i);
8547 
8548  }
8549  }
8550 
8551  /*--- We now have everything gathered by function name, so we can loop over
8552  each function and store the min/max times. ---*/
8553 
8554  int map_size = 0;
8555  for (map<string,vector<int> >::iterator it=Profile_Map_tp.begin(); it!=Profile_Map_tp.end(); ++it) {
8556  map_size++;
8557  }
8558 
8559  /*--- Allocate and initialize memory ---*/
8560 
8561  double *l_min_red, *l_max_red, *l_tot_red, *l_avg_red;
8562  int *n_calls_red;
8563  double* l_min = new double[map_size];
8564  double* l_max = new double[map_size];
8565  double* l_tot = new double[map_size];
8566  double* l_avg = new double[map_size];
8567  int* n_calls = new int[map_size];
8568  for (int i = 0; i < map_size; i++)
8569  {
8570  l_min[i] = 1e10;
8571  l_max[i] = 0.0;
8572  l_tot[i] = 0.0;
8573  l_avg[i] = 0.0;
8574  n_calls[i] = 0;
8575  }
8576 
8577  /*--- Collect the info for each function from the current rank ---*/
8578 
8579  int func_counter = 0;
8580  for (map<string,vector<int> >::iterator it=Profile_Map_tp.begin(); it!=Profile_Map_tp.end(); ++it) {
8581 
8582  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < (it->second).size(); i++) {
8583  n_calls[func_counter]++;
8584  l_tot[func_counter] += Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]];
8585  if (Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]] < l_min[func_counter])
8586  l_min[func_counter] = Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]];
8587  if (Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]] > l_max[func_counter])
8588  l_max[func_counter] = Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]];
8589 
8590  }
8591  l_avg[func_counter] = l_tot[func_counter]/((double)n_calls[func_counter]);
8592  func_counter++;
8593  }
8594 
8595  /*--- Now reduce the data ---*/
8596 
8597  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
8598  l_min_red = new double[map_size];
8599  l_max_red = new double[map_size];
8600  l_tot_red = new double[map_size];
8601  l_avg_red = new double[map_size];
8602  n_calls_red = new int[map_size];
8603  }
8604 
8605 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
8606  MPI_Reduce(n_calls, n_calls_red, map_size, MPI_INT, MPI_SUM, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
8607  MPI_Reduce(l_tot, l_tot_red, map_size, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_SUM, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
8608  MPI_Reduce(l_avg, l_avg_red, map_size, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_SUM, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
8609  MPI_Reduce(l_min, l_min_red, map_size, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MIN, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
8610  MPI_Reduce(l_max, l_max_red, map_size, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MAX, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
8611 #else
8612  memcpy(n_calls_red, n_calls, map_size*sizeof(int));
8613  memcpy(l_tot_red, l_tot, map_size*sizeof(double));
8614  memcpy(l_avg_red, l_avg, map_size*sizeof(double));
8615  memcpy(l_min_red, l_min, map_size*sizeof(double));
8616  memcpy(l_max_red, l_max, map_size*sizeof(double));
8617 #endif
8618 
8619  /*--- The master rank will write the file ---*/
8620 
8621  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
8622 
8623  /*--- Take averages over all ranks on the master ---*/
8624 
8625  for (int i = 0; i < map_size; i++) {
8626  l_tot_red[i] = l_tot_red[i]/(double)size;
8627  l_avg_red[i] = l_avg_red[i]/(double)size;
8628  n_calls_red[i] = n_calls_red[i]/size;
8629  }
8630 
8631  /*--- Now write a CSV file with the processed results ---*/
8632 
8633  char cstr[200];
8634  ofstream Profile_File;
8635  strcpy (cstr, "profiling.csv");
8636 
8637  /*--- Prepare and open the file ---*/
8638 
8639  Profile_File.precision(15);
8640  Profile_File.open(cstr, ios::out);
8641 
8642  /*--- Create the CSV header ---*/
8643 
8644  Profile_File << "\"Function_Name\", \"N_Calls\", \"Avg_Total_Time\", \"Avg_Time\", \"Min_Time\", \"Max_Time\", \"Function_ID\"" << endl;
8645 
8646  /*--- Loop through the map and write the results to the file ---*/
8647 
8648  func_counter = 0;
8649  for (map<string,vector<int> >::iterator it=Profile_Map_tp.begin(); it!=Profile_Map_tp.end(); ++it) {
8650 
8651  Profile_File << scientific << it->first << ", " << n_calls_red[func_counter] << ", " << l_tot_red[func_counter] << ", " << l_avg_red[func_counter] << ", " << l_min_red[func_counter] << ", " << l_max_red[func_counter] << ", " << (int)Profile_ID_tp[(it->second)[0]] << endl;
8652  func_counter++;
8653  }
8654 
8655  Profile_File.close();
8656 
8657  }
8658 
8659  delete [] l_min;
8660  delete [] l_max;
8661  delete [] l_avg;
8662  delete [] l_tot;
8663  delete [] n_calls;
8664  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
8665  delete [] l_min_red;
8666  delete [] l_max_red;
8667  delete [] l_avg_red;
8668  delete [] l_tot_red;
8669  delete [] n_calls_red;
8670  }
8671 
8672 #endif
8673 
8674 }

8679 
8680 #ifdef HAVE_MKL

8682 #elif HAVE_MPI
8683  *val_start_time = MPI_Wtime();
8684 #else
8685  *val_start_time = double(clock())/double(CLOCKS_PER_SEC);

8687

8692 void CConfig::GEMM_Tock(double val_start_time, int M, int N, int K) {
8693 
8694 #ifdef PROFILE
8695 
8696  /* Determine the timing value. The actual function called depends on
8697  the type of executable. */
8698  double val_stop_time = 0.0;
8699 
8700 #ifdef HAVE_MKL
8701  val_stop_time = dsecnd();
8702 #elif HAVE_MPI
8703  val_stop_time = MPI_Wtime();
8704 #else
8705  val_stop_time = double(clock())/double(CLOCKS_PER_SEC);
8706 #endif
8707 
8708  /* Compute the elapsed time. */
8709  const double val_elapsed_time = val_stop_time - val_start_time;
8710 
8711  /* Create the CLong3T from the M-N-K values and check if it is already
8712  stored in the map GEMM_Profile_MNK. */
8713  CLong3T MNK(M, N, K);
8714  map<CLong3T, int>::iterator MI = GEMM_Profile_MNK.find(MNK);
8715 
8716  if(MI == GEMM_Profile_MNK.end()) {
8717 
8718  /* Entry is not present yet. Create it. */
8719  GEMM_Profile_MNK[MNK] = GEMM_Profile_MNK.size();
8720 
8721  GEMM_Profile_NCalls.push_back(1);
8722  GEMM_Profile_TotTime.push_back(val_elapsed_time);
8723  GEMM_Profile_MinTime.push_back(val_elapsed_time);
8724  GEMM_Profile_MaxTime.push_back(val_elapsed_time);
8725  }
8726  else {
8727 
8728  /* Entry is already present. Determine its index in the
8729  map and update the corresponding vectors. */
8730  const int ind = MI->second;
8731  ++GEMM_Profile_NCalls[ind];
8732  GEMM_Profile_TotTime[ind] += val_elapsed_time;
8733  GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind] = min(GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind], val_elapsed_time);
8734  GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind] = max(GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind], val_elapsed_time);
8735  }
8736 
8737 #endif
8738 
8739 }
8740 
8741 void CConfig::GEMMProfilingCSV(void) {
8742 
8743 #ifdef PROFILE
8744 
8745  /* Initialize the rank to the master node. */
8746  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
8747 
8748 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
8749  /* Parallel executable. The profiling data must be sent to the master node.
8750  First determine the rank and size. */
8751  int size;
8752  SU2_MPI::Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
8753  SU2_MPI::Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &size);
8754 
8755  /* Check for the master node. */
8756  if(rank == MASTER_NODE) {
8757 
8758  /* Master node. Loop over the other ranks to receive their data. */
8759  for(int proc=1; proc<size; ++proc) {
8760 
8761  /* Block until a message from this processor arrives. Determine
8762  the number of entries in the receive buffers. */
8763  SU2_MPI::Status status;
8764  SU2_MPI::Probe(proc, 0, MPI_COMM_WORLD, &status);
8765 
8766  int nEntries;
8767  SU2_MPI::Get_count(&status, MPI_LONG, &nEntries);
8768 
8769  /* Allocate the memory for the receive buffers and receive the
8770  three messages using blocking receives. */
8771  vector<long> recvBufNCalls(nEntries);
8772  vector<double> recvBufTotTime(nEntries);
8773  vector<double> recvBufMinTime(nEntries);
8774  vector<double> recvBufMaxTime(nEntries);
8775  vector<long> recvBufMNK(3*nEntries);
8776 
8777  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufNCalls.data(), recvBufNCalls.size(),
8778  MPI_LONG, proc, 0, MPI_COMM_WORLD, &status);
8779  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufTotTime.data(), recvBufTotTime.size(),
8780  MPI_DOUBLE, proc, 1, MPI_COMM_WORLD, &status);
8781  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufMinTime.data(), recvBufMinTime.size(),
8782  MPI_DOUBLE, proc, 2, MPI_COMM_WORLD, &status);
8783  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufMaxTime.data(), recvBufMaxTime.size(),
8784  MPI_DOUBLE, proc, 3, MPI_COMM_WORLD, &status);
8785  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufMNK.data(), recvBufMNK.size(),
8786  MPI_LONG, proc, 4, MPI_COMM_WORLD, &status);
8787 
8788  /* Loop over the number of entries. */
8789  for(int i=0; i<nEntries; ++i) {
8790 
8791  /* Create the CLong3T from the M-N-K values and check if it is already
8792  stored in the map GEMM_Profile_MNK. */
8793  CLong3T MNK(recvBufMNK[3*i], recvBufMNK[3*i+1], recvBufMNK[3*i+2]);
8794  map<CLong3T, int>::iterator MI = GEMM_Profile_MNK.find(MNK);
8795 
8796  if(MI == GEMM_Profile_MNK.end()) {
8797 
8798  /* Entry is not present yet. Create it. */
8799  GEMM_Profile_MNK[MNK] = GEMM_Profile_MNK.size();
8800 
8801  GEMM_Profile_NCalls.push_back(recvBufNCalls[i]);
8802  GEMM_Profile_TotTime.push_back(recvBufTotTime[i]);
8803  GEMM_Profile_MinTime.push_back(recvBufMinTime[i]);
8804  GEMM_Profile_MaxTime.push_back(recvBufMaxTime[i]);
8805  }
8806  else {
8807 
8808  /* Entry is already present. Determine its index in the
8809  map and update the corresponding vectors. */
8810  const int ind = MI->second;
8811  GEMM_Profile_NCalls[ind] += recvBufNCalls[i];
8812  GEMM_Profile_TotTime[ind] += recvBufTotTime[i];
8813  GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind] = min(GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind], recvBufMinTime[i]);
8814  GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind] = max(GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind], recvBufMaxTime[i]);
8815  }
8816  }
8817  }
8818  }
8819  else {
8820 
8821  /* Not the master node. Create the send buffer for the MNK data. */
8822  vector<long> sendBufMNK(3*GEMM_Profile_NCalls.size());
8823  for(map<CLong3T, int>::iterator MI =GEMM_Profile_MNK.begin();
8824  MI!=GEMM_Profile_MNK.end(); ++MI) {
8825 
8826  const int ind = 3*MI->second;
8827  sendBufMNK[ind] = MI->first.long0;
8828  sendBufMNK[ind+1] = MI->first.long1;
8829  sendBufMNK[ind+2] = MI->first.long2;
8830  }
8831 
8832  /* Send the data to the master node using blocking sends. */
8833  SU2_MPI::Send(GEMM_Profile_NCalls.data(), GEMM_Profile_NCalls.size(),
8834  MPI_LONG, MASTER_NODE, 0, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
8835  SU2_MPI::Send(GEMM_Profile_TotTime.data(), GEMM_Profile_TotTime.size(),
8836  MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, 1, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
8837  SU2_MPI::Send(GEMM_Profile_MinTime.data(), GEMM_Profile_MinTime.size(),
8838  MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, 2, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
8839  SU2_MPI::Send(GEMM_Profile_MaxTime.data(), GEMM_Profile_MaxTime.size(),
8840  MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, 3, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
8841  SU2_MPI::Send(sendBufMNK.data(), sendBufMNK.size(),
8842  MPI_LONG, MASTER_NODE, 4, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
8843  }
8844 
8845 #endif
8846 
8847  /*--- The master rank will write the file ---*/
8848  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
8849 
8850  /* Store the elements of the map GEMM_Profile_MNK in
8851  vectors for post processing reasons. */
8852  const unsigned int nItems = GEMM_Profile_MNK.size();
8853  vector<long> M(nItems), N(nItems), K(nItems);
8854  for(map<CLong3T, int>::iterator MI =GEMM_Profile_MNK.begin();
8855  MI!=GEMM_Profile_MNK.end(); ++MI) {
8856 
8857  const int ind = MI->second;
8858  M[ind] = MI->first.long0;
8859  N[ind] = MI->first.long1;
8860  K[ind] = MI->first.long2;
8861  }
8862 
8863  /* In order to create a nicer output the profiling data is sorted in
8864  terms of CPU time spent. Create a vector of pairs for carrying
8865  out this sort. */
8866  vector<pair<double, unsigned int> > sortedTime;
8867 
8868  for(unsigned int i=0; i<GEMM_Profile_TotTime.size(); ++i)
8869  sortedTime.push_back(make_pair(GEMM_Profile_TotTime[i], i));
8870 
8871  sort(sortedTime.begin(), sortedTime.end());
8872 
8873  /* Open the profiling file. */
8874  char cstr[200];
8875  ofstream Profile_File;
8876  strcpy (cstr, "gemm_profiling.csv");
8877 
8878  Profile_File.precision(15);
8879  Profile_File.open(cstr, ios::out);
8880 
8881  /* Create the CSV header */
8882  Profile_File << "\"Total_Time\", \"N_Calls\", \"Avg_Time\", \"Min_Time\", \"Max_Time\", \"M\", \"N\", \"K\", \"Avg GFLOPs\"" << endl;
8883 
8884  /* Loop through the different items, where the item with the largest total time is
8885  written first. As sortedTime is sorted in increasing order, the sequence of
8886  sortedTime must be reversed. */
8887  for(vector<pair<double, unsigned int> >::reverse_iterator rit =sortedTime.rbegin();
8888  rit!=sortedTime.rend(); ++rit) {
8889  /* Determine the original index in the profiling vectors. */
8890  const unsigned int ind = rit->second;
8891  const double AvgTime = GEMM_Profile_TotTime[ind]/GEMM_Profile_NCalls[ind];
8892  const double GFlops = 2.0e-9*M[ind]*N[ind]*K[ind]/AvgTime;
8893 
8894  /* Write the data. */
8895  Profile_File << scientific << GEMM_Profile_TotTime[ind] << ", " << GEMM_Profile_NCalls[ind] << ", "
8896  << AvgTime << ", " << GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind] << ", " << GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind] << ", "
8897  << M[ind] << ", " << N[ind] << ", " << K[ind] << ", " << GFlops << endl;
8898  }
8899 
8900  /* Close the file. */
8901  Profile_File.close();
8902  }
8903 
8904 #endif
8905 
8906 }
